  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Generally, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - creating complex transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration - making the funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but generally involve:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained money\n- Transforming cash from criminal activities into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to hide the true ownership or nature of financial assets\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering laws?",
